## Example 5 — Compose Functions

Given:

* `f(x) = 2x - 5`
* `g(x) = 3x`

Find `[f o g](x)` and `[g o f](x)`. State the domain and range for each.

### Part A: Find the compositions

`[f o g](x) = f[g(x)] = f(3x) = 2(3x) - 5 = 6x - 5`

`[g o f](x) = g[f(x)] = g(2x - 5) = 3(2x - 5) = 6x - 15`

### Part B: Domain and range

Because both are linear functions with nonzero slopes:

* domain: all real numbers
* range: all real numbers

